<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-27T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857/58: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-27T20:00:00-05:00">February
                                    27, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>42. Department’s 39, February 26, 6 p.m. In order to expedite this
                            matter, the Department suggests that the Brazilian Government circulate
                            the text of the protest on the <hi rend="italic">Wakama</hi> incident
                            drafted by that Government to the other American Republics for their
                            approval. Please inform Aranha that the Department will be pleased to
                            assist in this matter, particularly in the case of countries where
                            Brazil has no diplomatic representation. In view of the time which has
                            elapsed since this incident, it is felt that the matter should be
                            handled by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>